caption: Su comida es sabrosa, tienen buenas porciones, es agradable el lugar y tranquilo. Que esperas amante de la comida ve a deleitarte con su sazón...

The service at this location is top notch. They went above and beyond to accommodate our bigger group with outdoor seating and brought all food out for us really quickly. The food is also delicious! (Beers not included - BYOB)
The food was delicious.

French toast rolls are like bulky sugar pencils...nothing of substance. The sweet tomale is very weird, the masa isn’t appetizing at all just colorful. The huevos a la mexicana was basically two tortillas, refried beans, eggs and onions. I could have made a fancier breakfast at home for less $$.
great food and great service!!!! tamales are very good

Mixed review here. The burrito was enormous, and was a good deal for $15. However, when you shove an entire burrito with mostly beans and rice, it tastes exactly like that, and should be that big. The taquitos were garbage. Extremely overcomes, half the taquitos weren’t even edible, they came out crunchier than tortilla chips, and the meat inside was grossly overcooked and inedible. For $10 and for only 4 of these, which only half was edible, is ridiculous. Lastly, the beef chorizo quesadilla was actually tasty. Definitely wouldn’t come back. Not worth $50 for sub par skimped mexican food.
Really delicious nachos and tamales.
Good takos

This is the most delicious thing I’ve ever put in my face. Juicy chicken, flavorful Spanish rice and beans, and even some chips in the bag! I ordered from seamless but had to post a review here as well. Best burrito bowl ever!!

Maya Taqueria is an awesome neighborhood go-to.  The menu is big and really unique and has so many options, especially for vegetarians.  Maya is our go-to spot for burritos and burrito bowls.  The staff is so friendly and food always comes quickly.  Maya is the kind of local Mexican place you hope to have in your hood.
The chicken tortilla soup was bomb!
Soggy chicken quesadilla. So disappointed

I often come here with my family for their authentic food. The flavors remind me of the food in California. We always order the regular or deluxe burrito with grilled or shredded chicken, spices, with everything on it! Simply love it!

I got a burrito and I suddenly was surprised that it has onions mixed with the salad. It doesn’t say that the burrito has onions mixed with other stuff and I was allergic to it. I asked the waitress to help with other recommendations and she did say that all their food is cooked with onions. Also, she was disrespectful and didn’t want to do the burrito again until I had to get angry and explain to her that it is the law that they should put the ingredients on each product. They even freaked me out more by saying that their rice and beans are COOKED with onions - so they have nothing to do about it. What should I have done? I was already late to work and I got super mad and I stormed out (without breaking the door as they mentioned, which is nothing but a complete lie).I apparently now know why in this country, suing people and corporations really worth it. I do not recommend this place. Such a horrible treatment and experience.
I feel like it’s ok but still disappointing somehow. I’ve tried it a few times to make sure I didn’t just get a bad burrito. It’s food that comes in a tortilla. May be some people’s jam.
Their super nachos are the bomb!!!

My favorite spot for a burrito in all of Brooklyn!  Always fresh, high quality ingredients. Owners is always available for questions and i you can see the pride and care he takes in making the food. Definite recommend for lunch, dinner or even late night!!!

I order a burrito bowl and they gave me a plastic platter. over all  the burrito was good but when I talk to the manager about it he was very  opinionated about the the plastic platter when its should be a tortilla Bowl.
Another great Mexican place in Brooklyn. We are very lucky to have amazing restaurants in NYC. I love this place!

I had an unbelievable experience during a time of  Need (6/3/20 @ 2:30pm)For the manager to be so rude/mean to another human is surreal, screaming at me like child and will not let me get a word in edgewise. I ordered $48. In food and the promotion was to receive a corn on the cob for free. I called back and let them know, the workers transferred me to the manager Daniel. The conservation consist of me saying "can I Please have the corn",Daniel said that grub hub promoted it and I was supposed to order the corn and It would have been deducted off the bill. So I asked "if I could have the corn, my children wanted it that's why I ordered the amount" he said "no!!! I should ask grub hub, they are a million dollar company and I should ask them" I asked if I could walk to the restaurant to get corn (i would have paid for it) he said "NO" then I said "I will not order from them ever again" he went nuts screaming at me. I was trying to tell him about communication, because I wrote a note on the delivery details saying "please don't forget to bring my free corn". But he was screaming about small businesses and he doesn't care about me. I was so up set and in tears I said "who the F are you to treat me like this" he could not have screamed any louder Goodbye!!!over and  over until he slammed the phone down... I saved our burrito for dinner, Now 8pm here we are eating and my little boy bites down on hard pice of broken resin plastic inside of the burrito... I dont dare call back... please be very careful and weary.... I support small businesses all the way just not vulgar, careless, dirty ones

I’ve been looking for a good burrito since moving to new york from cali. This is the closest to home I’ve had so far. Ordered the prawn burrito. A little on the pricey side but to be fair it was a massive burrito with lots of prawns! Ate half and saved the rest for the next day so definitely worth it. Chips were crispy and fresh. I’ll definitely be back to try the handmade tamales.

Unreliable. Be careful ordering delivery from here. Ordered delivery through Maya Taqueria and it never arrived. We called 30 minutes after it was supposed to arrive several times and no one ever answered. We’re still trying to get in contact to get our purchase refunded....

Delicious food!  But, even more importantly such a thoughtful staff.  I'm currently a breastfeeding mom and need to be soy and dairy free due to the baby's allergies and Daniel was so accommodating walking me through the menu and then personally guaranteeing he'd oversee our order.  This kind of service, especially in stressful times like these, is SO appreciated.  Please order through their website so they get all the profits, plus you get 10% off your first order and 5% off every order after that (this is not an ad, I swear, I just want to make sure good businesses keep getting business right now).  It's so hard to find soy and dairy free delivery right now and I just can't handle making dinner on my own every night.  So, from the bottom of my heart, thank you Daniel and the staff of of Maya Taqueria Park Slope.  Now I'm going to go and reheat the extra tamales I ordered!
Late night burrito stop & couldn't have been happier! Great service, clean establishment, delicious food, and they have a rewards system in place
Great Food!
Excellent food good hospitality.
Plates are HUGE, fair for the price, fresh ingredients, can't go wrong here.
One of the best burritos I've had in NYC! The ingredients are fresh. The service is great.
Priced to high for portion and quality of food.
The best quesadilla I’ve EVER had. Perod.

Ordered a chicken burritto to get delivered, and got mostly rice with little flavor. Also ordered chips and guac and got a ton of guac, but they just threw like 6 chips in the bag with the burrito. Real weird.
Ordered a steak burrito. Got mostly rice and almost no steak which was disappointing.

twice I had a burrito from here and both times they were great. They're pretty big and  I had to stuff them down. I'm picky when it comes to eating out  but I was working nearby and noticed how many times they were cleaning either the inside, the windows or the sidewalk. I also noticed another area of the building and the place was very clean.  I dont regularly eat mexican food but I liked what I had and would recommend it to anyone.
Where TF is the meat?  There is very little steak in the steak burrito
By far the best take-out taco place in the area.
Very good burrito. Really liked the salsa/sauce bar. Burrito wrap did not hold together well?
Food was phenomenal
1st time, was ok.
Loved the burritos here
Amazing portions and complimentary salsa!
Salsa bar was solid. Mushroom burrito could have been better

I have always been a fan of the place in Prospect Heights. Then I ordered from the one  Park slope. I had to repeat all of my information to the girl three times which is fine, annoying but ok. I asked for the different sauces on the side. She said to make up for the delay she would  include all the sauces. In reality I thought that this was a given but I thanked her. The burrito came it took almost an hour when she said it would take 20 mins. Unlike the prospect heights location the  ingredients did not taste fresh and the burrito fell apart within seconds , it was gross. Also they didn’t give me a single sauce.  I guess this restaurants  management and quality has really gone down, what a shame.
Loved their tasty filling tacos! +E Recording artist- Edwin Vazquez
Just ordered their takeout and got a very tasty, spicy California burrito and the best refried beans I've had in ages. Will definitely order from them again!
Tasty
Delicious and pricey.
Nice authentic Spanish food. Very fresh and plentiful servings
Good service and food was good. Pretty quick from order to take out.

FRESH!!! first thought, TASTY!!! second thought, Warm/comforting/filling, worth the price, third thought!! The warm homemade chips thrown in the bag as a bonus 🙌🙌🙌 Definitely going back! Had a vegan bowl and it was so dee-lish!😋😋😋 Free salsa bar👍
1st time eating here. I should had taken my time looking at the menu.
The food is good and customer service is pleasant
Great place to grab a bite. Friednsly staff and clean establishment.
Tacos were okay. Mole was too sweet. Good if you're in the neighborhood, wouldn't go out of my way to come here.
I’m so happy to have discovered a place with deliciously marinated and shredded chicken mole! The chicken mole burrito is amazing, and so is the salsa bar. Can’t wait to try everything on the menu!
Maya Taqueria serves the best Mexican food in the area and the customer service is excellent.
Really good central American food. Many choices of salsa

I’ve been here a few times and I am unimpressed. The tacos are ok. Not the best, not the worst. It really depends on the day and time you go. Definitely better than Chipotle.  The sides are lackluster. One time I spilled my drink and asked for napkins so I could clean it up. The cashier literally gave me 1 napkin. Other times, the staff is super helpful. Really depends on when you go.

Didn't hate it.  Didn't love it. I got the fried camaròn taco. It sounded interesting that they deep fry the shell and shrimp but in the end it was just fried and dry. I probably ordered the wrong thing so hopefully I'll be able to update this review next time.  The staff was very friendly though.
Tasty wholesome food! Everyone was extra polite and very friendly! Great portions and very reasonable prices! Looking forward to going back!  The also have Gluten free options!
Tacos were delicious! Could use a bit more sitting space, but the tacos were delicious and there's a huge selection of meats and toppings. Make sure you ask for extra napkins.
Cheap and good
service is mediocre, food is excellent
Very good and inexpensive .
Dominant
Low quality Mexican
Fave burritos, best taqueria in the park slope bk area.

This place is alright, but the service takes too long and thats where they lose 2 stars right off the bat. I like mexican food and they are pretty much latinos in this joint, but I was starving for almost half an hour...sorry but I honestly can't recommend this place due to the lack of service...to the customer at hand. The service seems to be much faster on takeout customers and that's ok. Just don't make it look like a restaurant if it isn't and carter only to pre-orders. I get that thats the bulk of your income, but how are you going to grow you income without getting more people to attend yom
Try their burritos with shredded chicken in mole sauce! The mayans were one of the first civilizations to use chocolate in their food – this is the closest you'll get in NYC!
Loved my burrito!

After living in Prospect Heights for several years eating at the original Maya, I was thrilled they opened this second one in Park Slope. Sadly this second location isn't nearly as good as the original location. We've ordered from here many times and the food has always been inconsistent some days being good and other days not, or they mess up our order when we pick it up. Their guacamole and chips was a staple item we always got in Prospect Heights, but this Park Slope one lacks flavor a lot, or is watery. The beef has been pretty fatty lately (by that I mean chunks of fat on the meat) and the rice mushy.  I keep going hoping for better food that they'd have their footing by now, but no more. I'd say people should go to the original location on Vanderbilt. Way better than this location.
Pretty awesome burritos and tacos for a pretty reasonable price

This little shop is a big success in my book. For fast and tasty Mexican food, you can’t beat Maya. I highly recommend the Danny Danny burrito as a bowl with steamed kale and onion and chicken al pastor. Really, really good.
Great food, great service, fresh food, at a good price. Park Slope location is better than Prospect Heights.
Very authentic food. People are kind and food is fresh.
Love there shrimp tacos platter
Food and service is great
Okay tacos
Food is good salsa and the jalapeno  is great
The Que Pasa burrito is bigger than your dog

Really good burritos and tamales and the staff is nice. A simple set up with quick service. They offer four tires of salsa, including green, chipotle, another spicy red and one called "princess" which is, exactly as described "spicy but tasty." The burritos come with a handful of chips and the tamales with a tasty red sauce. Fresh juices including horchata are seasonally available.
The tacos themselves were tasty. The place is pretty pricey. There is free salsa available  but no free chips. Most tacos come dry. Its is extra for sour cream  guac, etc
The food was very good but pricy.
This place was awesome until 4 friends and I felt instantly sick after eatting.
great neighborhood mexican
Great place, great food, great value compared to other restaurants. Very good portion size.

Happy this opened in Park Slope. I used to travel to Washington Ave to get their chips. The new local spot is great. Prices seem to have gone up, so I docked one star. They make their chips in house- at least fry them- which is probably why my addiction exists. I have only tried their chips, black beans and guacamole and all was delicious. Salsa bar is serious with some hot hot hot salsas worth trying. The main dishes are huge, and easily shareable. Staff is friendly and accommodating for any changes to your order. Will be here frequently and possibly try other items than chips.
The price is right and super close to my job. Great food!!!
I bought 3 tacos they were bad  no sauce they cold dry no way garbage is anything better around?
Very good food for a very low price.

I think some of the biggest praise that can be offered to this place is from my San Francisco native girlfriend who said that while many places claim to be "Mission style" this place actually is. The chips are clearly made from tortillas in house and it shows. The salsa bar and guac are fantastic and all the food totally delivered on flavor and serving size. My only complaint is that they did not have napkins out for the taking, but they gave us more when we asked so not a huge deal.
Solid cheap Latin food.

Prawn taco: don't waste your time. Only 2 of them. Over cooked & rubbery.  Chicken al pastor taco: I did not like. Fish taco: now that was tasty & loved the sauce. IF I ever order from this place again, that's all I'll get. But I highly doubt it. I asked for no cilantro, but I still got some. Lastly the homemade chips: a lot more than I expected.
Very tasty.  Authentic Mexican salsa bar.  Some creative veggie options.  Reasonably priced.  This will be a regular spot for me now.
I got the mushroom vegetarian burrito and it was great. The burrito was huge, reasonably priced and tasted great. Will be coming back to try more options

Went in with high hopes and sadly my expectations were not at all met. I went for the pollo al pastor burrito and there was probably two slivers of pineapple in the whole thing and the chicken was rather dry.  As an insult to injury I was served with an apparently generous side helping of 5 chips. Let's just say there is room for improvement.
Fantastic and tasty!  What could be better? Good prices too. Yeah, 5 gold stars!

Ordered online and got an email saying order would be ready at 7:43pm. When we arrived, it was not ready, no worries. Waited around as all the people who placed order after us got their food. Obviously, our order was never started until we asked for it at the time of pick up. We even tried to call to make sure they got our order but of course their phone number was also not in service. Not sure how you open for business without a working phone number. When we finally got our food, there was no guac in the burrito as ordered. Food quality is meh. We live right around the corner too. If it was good, we would have been a regular. Too bad. Never going back.  Especially when there is Oaxaca right on 4th Ave which has comparably much better mexican food, not to mention the taco truck on Union st.
